@demographics
go-to: menu

**Demographic Groups**

**Working Class**: The urban working class - blue-collar workers in factories, workshops, mines, and the like. Most are socialist, supporting the SAPM or SPM. They make up 35 - 45% of the population.

**Old Mittelstand**: The old middle class consists of independent artisans, shopkeepers, and small-time businesspeople. They tend to be conservative/liberal and are the strongest base for the right and the liberals. 12-18% of the population.

**New Mittelstand**: The new middle class consists of white-collar workers and government employees. This is the base of progressive liberalism. 15-20% of the population.

**Rural**: Larger farmers and independent rural workers. Those farmers often support the MNVP or LDP. 15-20% of the population.

**Peasants**: Poor farmers and landless peasants. Most are demand land reform, supporting the ASUM or GDSU. 15-20% of the population.

**Catholics** are the dominant religious group, at about 60% of the population. (in order to not make a big blob gropu they represnet those hard line religous people not associated with a economic class)

**Minorites** make up around 10% of the population, they mostly live in Percil (Percilians) and in the south (Lacossians and Radorrians) predominatly support the PPU and their subparties.

